cs.SC, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.CG 

This paper is likely to belong to cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) as it deals with improving the performance of Cylindrical Algebraic Decomposition (CAD), which is a key tool in computational algebraic geometry. The use of machine learning (specifically support vector machines) to make choices in CAD variable ordering and Grobner Basis preconditioning suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper involves analyzing data and making decisions based on learned properties, which could also place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper deals with geometric relationships, which could make it relevant to cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
